{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"RECOMMENDED\n    1\n    \n      Thin React Shell — Extensions Are Components\n      The shell is a React layout engine. Extensions export React components that mount into named slots. No process separation. Everything in one renderer.\n\n      \n      \n        /* Electron Renderer (one Chromium process) */\n        \n          React Shell\n          \n            ├─ ext-amplifier-canvas → mounts Canvas slot\n            ├─ ext-git-panel → mounts Sidebar slot\n            └─ ext-status-items → mounts StatusBar slot\n          \n        \n        /* Extension author writes: */\n        export default { manifest, Canvas, SidebarPanel }\n      \n\n      \n        Pros\n          Zero friction — one export, done\n          Hot reload works automatically\n          Share React context, Zustand stores\n          Cloud-portable (no Node.js APIs in extensions)\n        \n        Trade-offs\n          Extension crash → shell crash\n          No process isolation for marketplace\n          (fixable later with sandbox layer)","choice":"1","id":null,"timestamp":1776740641814}
